# Fluvio CLI Testing

## Overview

The CLI testing is written using the [bats-core](https://bats-core.readthedocs.io/en/stable/index.html) framework. Follow their [instructions ](https://bats-core.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html) for installation.

The basic way to run tests is with the following command:

`bats <path to your-test.bats>`



### Test helper descriptions

There are bats libraries and example config files in the `test_helper` directory. The following are a description of a few of the commonly used libraries.

#### tools_check.bash
This is where to place tests for ensuring that any required tools are installed

#### fluvio_dev.bash
This is where any common functions are organized for using in your tests. 

